ClassDesc: A NumericShaper.Range represents a Unicode range of a script having its own decimal digits. For example, the @B_java#awt#font#NumericShaper#Range#THAI_E@ range has the Thai digits, THAI DIGIT ZERO (U+0E50) to THAI DIGIT NINE (U+0E59). The Range enum replaces the traditional bit mask-based values (e.g., @B_java#awt#font#NumericShaper#ARABIC_E@), and supports more Unicode ranges than the bit mask-based ones.
